#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "48. Uyyuttasenāsikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 48: the training rule on armies in action"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.48.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.374"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa981"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo senāya abbhuyyāto hoti."
msgstr "At that time King Pasenadi of Kosala was marching out with the army,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "and the monks from the group of six went to see the army in action."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo chabbaggiye bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante."
msgstr "King Pasenadi saw those monks coming,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Disvāna pakkosāpetvā etadavoca—"
msgstr "and he summoned them and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, bhante, āgatatthā”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerables, why have you come here?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Mahārājānaṃ mayaṃ daṭṭhukāmā → mahārāja mahārājānaṃ mayaṃ daṭṭhukāmā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“Mahārājānaṃ mayaṃ daṭṭhukāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We wish to see the great king.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: yuddhābhinandinaṃ → yud­dhā­bhinan­diṃ (bj) | yud­dhā­bhinan­dinā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“Kiṃ, bhante, maṃ diṭṭhena yuddhābhinandinaṃ;"
msgstr "“What’s the use of seeing me finding pleasure in battle?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "nanu bhagavā passitabbo”ti?"
msgstr "Shouldn’t you see the Master?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And people grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya āgacchissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics go to see an army in action?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā senāya āgacchāmā”ti."
msgstr "It’s our misfortune that we must go out with the army for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa982"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six go to see an army in action?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you go to see an army in action?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.22a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.375"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa983"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk goes to see an army in action, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa984"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.105"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.48.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa985"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno mātulo senāya gilāno hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a certain monk had a sick uncle in the army."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "So tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "The uncle sent a message to that monk:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“ahañhi senāya gilāno."
msgstr "“I’m with the army and I’m sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "Āgacchatu bhadanto."
msgstr "Please come, Venerable;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Icchāmi bhadantassa āgatan”ti."
msgstr "I want you to come.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Atha kho tassa bhikkhuno etadahosi—“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—‘na uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gantabban’ti."
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had laid down a rule against going to see an army in action, that monk thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Ayañca me mātulo senāya gilāno."
msgstr "“I have an uncle in the army who is sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "What should I do?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tathārūpappaccayā senāya gantuṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to go to the army when there’s a suitable reason."

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.12a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa986"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. VARL tathārūpappaccayā → … rūpapaccayā (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gaccheyya, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk goes to see an army in action, unless there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "(<em>48</em>:<strong>97</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.48.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.48.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa987"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa988"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Uyyuttā nāma"
msgstr "An army in action:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "senā gāmato nikkhamitvā niviṭṭhā vā hoti payātā vā."
msgstr "it has left the village and is either encamped or marching."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa989"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Senā nāma"
msgstr "An army:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "hatthī assā rathā pattī."
msgstr "elephants, horses, chariots, infantry."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Dvādasapuriso hatthī, tipuriso asso, catupuriso ratho, cattāro purisā sarahatthā patti."
msgstr "Each elephant has twelve men; each horse has three men; each chariot has four men; each unit of infantry has four men with arrows in hand."

#. </span>
#. </p><hr><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.376"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid "Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is on his way to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "Every time he moves outside of the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa990"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Aññatra tathārūpappaccayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is a suitable reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "ṭhapetvā tathārūpappaccayaṃ."
msgstr "except if there is a suitable reason."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.48.3.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa991"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid "Uyyutte uyyuttasaññī dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is in action, and he perceives it as in action, and he goes to see it, unless there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid "Uyyutte vematiko dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is in action, but he is unsure if it is, and he goes to see it, unless there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid "Uyyutte anuyyuttasaññī dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is in action, but he does not perceive it as in action, and he goes to see it, unless there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa992"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is on his way to see one division of a fourfold army, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "Every time he moves outside of the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Anuyyutte uyyuttasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not in action, but he perceives it as in action, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.8"
msgid "Anuyyutte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not in action, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.2.9"
msgid "Anuyyutte anuyyuttasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not in action, and he does not perceive it as in action, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.48.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa993"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "ārāme ṭhito passati,"
msgstr "if he sees it while standing in the monastery;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgacchati,"
msgstr "if the army comes to where the monk happens to be standing, sitting, or lying down;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "paṭipathaṃ gacchanto passati,"
msgstr "if he sees it while walking in the opposite direction;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "tathārūpappaccayā,"
msgstr "if he has a suitable reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa994"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc48:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "Uyyuttasenāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on armies in action, is finished."

